<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-1E95BDBB-A73F-49E7-9E2F-24A7C496890D" version="1" lang="en-US"?><reference xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-1E95BDBB-A73F-49E7-9E2F-24A7C496890D" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic reference)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c reference oceReference-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic       reference/reference "><title class="- topic/title ">19 Explanation Winding modes and when to use</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-24D550D7-7054-4B6D-83E3-EC11A87279FE"><p class="- topic/p "> This page explains the purpose of the three winding modes. After reading, you will better understand why more than one mode is offered and when to choose which mode. </p><p class="- topic/p ">Goal is also to trigger you there is an important relation to print quality depending on the winding mode.</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><refbody class="- topic/body        reference/refbody "><section id="GUID-B3031E52-E8C8-4AD7-9379-D18B5359AC10" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview winding modes</title><table id="GUID-D69A6861-D82B-486B-BC19-9426328400D8" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="8" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="11*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="11*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="11*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="23*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="16*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="17*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col7" colnum="7" colwidth="16*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col8" colnum="8" colwidth="17*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tight Blouse Winding</p></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loose Blouse Winding</p></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Locked Tension bar Winding</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-39AD3226-01FF-4BBA-A573-DF969620B02B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B5A72F31-78A8-4E0E-9197-C5F269CA8329-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B5A72F31-78A8-4E0E-9197-C5F269CA8329-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-0417BDC3-DFE3-48ED-AD8C-809FFD9EC7F7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-24074BA5-DDE7-4A38-AF3F-303335F9CD33-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-24074BA5-DDE7-4A38-AF3F-303335F9CD33-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-BC675A91-B7FD-4630-8E35-65B709DC4E21" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5B6A24F7-22A2-418D-931B-0AFB52465C7B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5B6A24F7-22A2-418D-931B-0AFB52465C7B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C7EE0D81-21EC-4DF1-936F-D90BA74C9E10" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CB399108-361F-4D8D-9528-A8F2645B24AE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CB399108-361F-4D8D-9528-A8F2645B24AE-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Media transport pinch</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9A2E4E61-7362-47A0-839F-6691709B3E20" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9AD985A1-B644-4ED3-B58B-C9F92434950B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9AD985A1-B644-4ED3-B58B-C9F92434950B-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= print surface (platen)</p></entry><entry colname="col3" namest="col3" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EBAEA1BC-85BF-4940-98C9-D83EFAA33E8D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3DD73593-32D9-484D-A2D5-33B761D72019-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3DD73593-32D9-484D-A2D5-33B761D72019-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Blouse forming bar</p></entry><entry colname="col5" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-50B98517-1DEA-40EB-ABAC-7DB5633C9225" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-CD469084-9D98-44DF-A5A9-E042E800DF3D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CD469084-9D98-44DF-A5A9-E042E800DF3D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Guide/Clamp</p></entry><entry colname="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7D1B7289-DAF4-4E2E-AAA2-987C5A9CCABE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BD70AB5B-1BF8-46A1-A773-1A01B75803FB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BD70AB5B-1BF8-46A1-A773-1A01B75803FB-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Take-up roll</p></entry><entry colname="col7" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-64FBD56E-E160-482D-96A7-6B93A5163E4C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EA12CABF-F73A-420D-B4E5-7BDC5B8B8563-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EA12CABF-F73A-420D-B4E5-7BDC5B8B8563-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Tension bar</p></entry><entry colname="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F3B41A73-0D73-40FF-B287-64F6EDAEEF23" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B9CE2F2F-C9B8-4B3D-9067-9325477CAC0C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B9CE2F2F-C9B8-4B3D-9067-9325477CAC0C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">= Medium</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Benefits</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Allows you to run really low print surface fan settings to prevent buckling</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Accommodates printing on weak/stretchy media by an additional pulling force in the blouse</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Benefits</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Printing from the leading edge</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Accommodates a large range of media</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Low stress/strain in the medium reduces the risk for visible banding artifacts</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Benefits</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Can create and maintain a blouse in stiff media</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Without low stress/strain in the medium during printing as with loose blouse winding</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media properties</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">weak</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">stretchable</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media properties</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Moderate stiffness</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Non-stretchable</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media properties</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Stiff</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Non-stretchable</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media range</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Canvas</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Textile</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Regular and heavy banner</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media range</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Light and regular paper</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Self adhesive paper, vinyl and canvas</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Light banner</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Thin film</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical media range</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">(Thick) film</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Heavy paper</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Backlit media</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" namest="col1" nameend="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical print surface (platen) fan settings</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone1: 30-100%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 2 and 3: 15-50%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 4 and 5: 0-30%</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col5" namest="col5" nameend="col6" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical print surface (platen) fan settings</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone1: 40-70%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 2 and 3: 40-60%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 4 and 5: 30-50%</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col7" namest="col7" nameend="col8" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Typical print surface (platen) fan settings</b></p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone1: 50-80%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 2 and 3: 50-80%</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Zone 4 and 5: 50-80%</p></li></ul></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-5C658B9B-6339-4549-A9E4-1AECE7E851ED" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Tight blouse winding</title><p class="- topic/p "> Tight winding extends the winding capabilities towards 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">weaker and stretchy media</b>, such as canvas and heavy banners. </p><p class="- topic/p ">These media require a pulling force to be able to travel over the print surface (platen), which is realized by a 2,5kg tension bar in the blouse. </p><p class="- topic/p ">Since the tension is required from the start, 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">leading edge printing is impossible</b> in case of tight blouse winding.</p></section><section id="GUID-E77A66ED-4FA4-47B5-BBD7-FC1BFD631C5F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Loose blouse winding</title><p class="- topic/p "> Loose winding is the preferred winding strategy for many paper, self-adhesive, film and banner media, considered moderately stiff and relatively flat. </p><p class="- topic/p ">These kinds of media can be pushed over the print surface (platen) without buckling, which makes it possible to 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">print close to the leading edge with decent winding quality.</b> </p></section><section id="GUID-C6EBB4E5-D0AE-4F6C-85A2-26B77B92985D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Locked Tension bar Winding</title><p class="- topic/p "> Many Stiff media like thick films and heavy paper only require a large bending force during the creation of the blouse. </p><p class="- topic/p ">Since the standard bar for blouse forming is too light and it cannot deliver that such bending force together with the media transport pinch. </p><p class="- topic/p ">To overcome this, the tension bar can also purely act as a "heavy" blouse forming bar. </p><p class="- topic/p ">The tension bar, in this case, is not required after blouse creation. </p><p class="- topic/p ">A locking mechanism will keep it at the top and out of the blouse during printing. </p><p class="- topic/p ">Due to its weight, the tension bar has too much interaction with the media transport pinch during blouse formation. Therefore, 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">leading edge printing is impossible</b> in case of locked tension bar winding<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">.</b> </p></section><section id="GUID-B0B220B1-A85E-4ABB-A2D6-90A79EFD2B4B" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> In terms of latitude, the 3 strategies have some overlap. </title><p class="- topic/p ">Certain media will be printable in both tight as well loose winding mode, however in such case one will notice differences in print and/or winding quality. </p><p class="- topic/p ">Also, the majority of "loose winding media" are perfectly printable with locked tension bar winding, but since you will lose the possibility to print on the leading edge and get nothing in return, this is not recommended.</p><fig id="GUID-0DF79A07-194D-4B9E-95BC-23ADE8170135" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A98E9098-EA84-46BF-B0BC-7DD424BA278D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A98E9098-EA84-46BF-B0BC-7DD424BA278D-low.png"/></fig></section></refbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
